#1 Clone the Git repository 
   git clone git@github.com:mathematikboy/Symfony-Addressbook.git

#2 Install PHP if not installed 
   https://www.php.net/manual/en/install.php
   php version must be 7.4+. 	
#3 Install composer if you haven't installed it.
   https://getcomposer.org/download/

#4 Install SQLITE 
    https://www.sqlitetutorial.net/download-install-sqlite/
	https://www.sqlite.org/2021/sqlite-tools-win32-x86-3340100.zip
	If you have just installed the SQLITE, Don't forget to uncomment the sqlite driver for php. 
	It should be something like follwoing in php.ini file localed at php folder. To determine where 
	the location of php: you can use the command ,,where php".  
	;extension=pdo_pgsql
	extension=pdo_sqlite 
	;extension=pgsql
	;extension=shmop
	
#5 Install Symfony if you havent installed before 
	https://symfony.com/download

#6 Go to the project folder that you have cloned before. 
  Symfony-Addressbook 
	
#7 Execute the following command 
   composer install 
   symfony serve 
#8 Start adding more Addresses and Try to filtem them by name , city or postal code 

#9 If there are any problems during installation, please let me know. 

